SAILORS' talk is a dialect as distinct from ordinary English 
as is Lowland Scotch. Certainly, English words are used, 
but their signification is many times remote from the 
meaning they have in shore parlance. The meaning of 
many sea-phrases is too subtle for translation ; some fit 

