was very agreeably surprised at the effect of some of these 
chanty choruses ; some of the men present had really good 
voices, and they sang with a life and spirit, and with as 
much rhythmical accuracy as though they were miles 
away on the briny ocean " heaving the windlass round, or 
hoisting the ponderous anchor." 

