HAULING CHANTIES. 

Of these, there is first the hand-over-hand song, in very 
quick time ; then the long-pull song, when there are, per- 
haps, twenty or thirty men pulling on a rope. To be 
effective, the pull must be made unanimously. This is 
secured by the chanty, the pulling made at some parti- 
