verse the word "handy "is the signal, at each repetition, 
for a long pull, a strong pull, and a pull all together : 
Chorus. Oh, shake her up, and away we'll go, 

So handy, my girls, so handy ; 
Up aloft from down below, 

So handy, my girls, so handy. 

For heavier work, or where hands are few, one of longer 
metre is used, such as " O Long Storm, storm along, 
Stormy," which must not, however, be confounded with 
the capstan chanty, " Old Storm Along." 

