' Jack/ for such he was, was equally at home with the waltz, 
but when a gavotte was played his terpsichorean antics were 
brought to a sudden close. In vain he tried to keep time to 
the air ; but after giving a few more coppers to the woman, 
he was suited with a schottische. The climax was, however, 
reached when the ' Marseillaise' was ground out. ' Jack ' 
