that makes the beauty of the art, and for much of its 
science. Overflowing with natural beauty, rich in historical 
associations, and in relics which set these forth, peopled by 
those who are brimful of natural aptitude and that quick 
nervous sensibility which is so important an element of 
musical genius, who does not look to Italy as the " Land 
of Harmony," with its fascinating coast-line, its northern 
lakes, Naples with its beautiful bay, and Venice with its 
lazy lagoons ? 

