There is no nation in the world prouder of its national 
ensign than is Denmark of its Dann<brog not even 
England of her Union Jack. Of this Dannebrog there is 
a curious legend, or rather, I should say, history. During 
the Valdemarian period the Danes now turned propagan- 
dists of Christianity, and during the war they waged against 
the pagan countries on the south and east of the Baltic, in 
one of the battles fought near Reval, in Russia, in the year 
1219, a great miracle is said to have occurred. They had 



