discarded the old pagan flag of the raven, a new one was 
vouchsafed them by Heaven and sent down to them 
under this they became victorious. It was a red flag with 
a white cross, still the national ensign by sea and land. 

Amongst the Danish national songs there is one com- 
memorative of this : 

" The Danndbrog, 'tis known, 
The Dannebrog, 'tis known, 
It fell from Heaven down ; 
Yes, it fell from Heaven down ! 
It floats upon the mast, 
The soldier grasps it fast. 
