band's : they also till the soil, make the hay, spin the hemp 
for the rigging, and bleach the linen. In these varied and 
complicated duties the housewife has no servant to assist 
her, all has to be done by one pair of hands. Truly the 
women of Marken must be deserving of that often mis- 
quoted title of "housewife;" the making and not the 
marring of a happy home surely lies in the sturdy, indus- 
trious helpmeets of the Marken fishermen. 

