matelot at Nantes or Bordeaux cease his song, and refuse 
to join in quaffing the rich juices afforded by the vintage 
of the Garonne, or will the Yankee sailor of Massachusetts, 
or the Bucksin of ' ole Virginny,' fail less to kick at the 
dispiriting measures of the select, social, temporal teeto- 
talers," who, he avers, would drive all sociability into " an 
eternal everlasting fix." 



