Many of the fishing community are of a decidedly 
religious character, thus following the example of their 
patron saint, St. Peter. Oftentimes on a summer's evening, 
off the Cornish coast, one may hear the fishermen engaged 
in singing hymns of praise. Like the Dutch seafaring 
men, these Cornish men are most fervent in their devotions ; 
