glorifying its blue breast with the gleam and colour of the 
enchanted island, gazing awe-struck about him as. he sailed 
along, and willing to believe anything he was told. I 
could give you no better illustration of this than the 
remark of the Jesuit, Anthony Sepp, in his account of a 
